latestPosts.caption:
100% Heatless Sock Curls 🧦💆🏻‍♀️😴

Woke up with the easiest curls—no heat, no damage, just soft, bouncy waves 🙂‍↕️😍👯‍♀️

Here’s what you need to know:👇

💦Keep your hair slightly damp (use a cream-based serum, leave-in conditioner, or just a little water)
🧦Fuzzy socks work best—less friction, no breakage & comfy to sleep in! (prefer an unused one🫢)
🎀Wrap your hair tight and flat—no gaps for the best curls
✨Before opening, run a serum through your hair for extra smoothness & shine

And that’s literally it! If you haven’t tried it yet, this is your cue gurlllll💌💤

IB- @singh.jessicaa 🥰

Read caption 🤍🦢🪞✨

It took me exactly 20 days to finalize that one outfit—because let’s be real, I’m extremely picky. I wanted something different, something customized, something me. Something like a Sharara—because roka is probably the only time (as compared to other wedding functions) I’d get to wear one.

I had a vision— a western-inspired sharara with a dupatta, something dainty yet comfortable enough to move (and maybe even jump) around in all day. 

Meeting his family for the first time, I wanted to feel confident and modest, without the weight of heavy embroidery or gold/silver tones. And guess what? This outfit turned out exactly how I imagined—the dream look! ✨

A little reminder for brides to be: On days like these, it’s not about whether people around you love your outfit. What matters is that you feel like the best version of yourself. And trust me, that energy is unmatched!❤️

Which one would you have picked and why? Let’s chat in the comments below 💌
